# Places Around Me
# Aim:
To develop a website to display details about the places around my house.

# Design Steps:
## Step 1
Create new django project

## Step 2
First Create the Folders and then input the code to create file.

## Step 3
Take screenshot for Google Map your location and decide minimum 5 places and create static file and create the website file.


# Code:

```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>Ulundurpet</title>
        <style>
            
            .images{
                display: flex;
                padding: 50px;
            }
            .p1{
                width: 300px;
                height: 250px;
                padding: 10px;
            }

                width: 260px;

                padding: 10px;

            }
            .p3{
                width: 250px;
                height: 250px;
                padding: 10px;

            }
            ul{
                font-size: 2rem;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>Ulundurpet</h1>
        <br>
        <div class="images">
        <img class="p1" src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTkwFE64hd1t2Ge2ilMGCx9unLCDNrPgkQRZeWMc29Zaw&s" alt="Ulundupet images">
        <img class="p2" src="https://i.ytimg.com/vi/Tg_m3dbx1PM/maxresdefault.jpg">
        <img class="p3" src="https://gumlet.vikatan.com/vikatan%2F2022-05%2F9cf2ae6a-c560-4942-8ac4-335428788819%2FIMG_20220512_WA0015_1652342330515.jpg?auto=format%2Ccompress&w=400&dpr=2.6"></div>

        <ul>
            <li>Ulundurpettai or Ulundurpet is a Municipality in Ulundurpet taluk of kallakurichi district of Tamil Nadu, India.</li>
            <li>It is at the intersection of NH 68 and NH 45 located 205 km from Chennai and 129 km from Tiruchirappalli.</li>
            <li>Ulundurpettai itself is a Constituency for Tamil Nadu State Assembly, and is the Taluk headquarters for Ulundurpet taluka in the eastern region of Kallakurichi district, and is in Ulundurpet revenue block.</li>
            <li>The Panchayat Town also has a railway station connecting Villupuram Junction, Villupuram and Virudhachalam Junction, Virudhachalam.- Ulundurpet railway station.</li>
            <li>Ulundurpet was once the home for Palyagar . The remains of the mud fort are still to be seen.</li>
            <li>The name Ulundurpettai is derived from the Saivaite temple currently called as Mashapureeswarar temple, located in the area Ulundandar Kovil , dedicated to Ulundandar or the Lord of the black-gram.</li>
            <li>As of 2011 India census, the town of Ulundurpettai had a population of 23,734. </li>
            <li>Males constituted 50% of the population and females 50%. </li>
            <li>Ulundurpettai had an average literacy rate of 71%, higher than the national average of 59.5%: male literacy was 79%, and female literacy was 63%. As of 2011 in Ulundurpettai, 12% of the population was under 6 years of age.</li>
            <li>Ulundurpet is one of the state assembly constituencies in Tamil Nadu. </li> 

    </body>
</html>
```

        <h1>Ulundurpet Bus Stand</h1>
        <br>
        <div class="images">
        <img class="p1" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="bus stop image">
        <img class="p2" src="https://i.ytimg.com/vi/vBcYr3vM8ds/hqdefault.jpg">
        <img class="p3" src="https://content.jdmagicbox.com/comp/villupuram/h7/9999p4146.4146.181128104355.k5h7/catalogue/ulundurpet-bus-stand-ulundurpet-villupuram-ua7ayfdkq7.jpg?clr=333333"></div>

        <ul>
            <li>Ulundupet bus stand is the main junction in chennai to trichy and chennai to salem highways</li>
            <li>There are numerous buses available at anytime to travel anywhere</li>
            <li>Many shops are available near bus stand</li>
            <li>The main advantage of this bus stop is that we can find many buses to travel</li>
            <li>Every buses from Chennai, Salem, Trichy and Madurai should get into the Bus stand to go anywhere</li>
            <li>There is a bus for chennai and trichy for every 5 minutes</li>
            <li>There is a bus depot in Ulundupet to park the buses</li>
            <li>It was located 1 km away from the Bus stand</li>
            <li>There is a biggest Toll plaza in National Highways located in Ulundupet</li>
             

    </body>
</html>

    <body>
        <h1>Hotel Vasandha Bhavan</h1>
        <br>
        <div class="images">
        <img class="p1" src="https://images.jdmagicbox.com/comp/villupuram/v5/9999p4146.4146.181101123321.g4v5/catalogue/hotel-vasantha-bhavan-ulundurpet-villupuram-restaurants-1l1uyynsxn.jpg?clr=" alt="Vasantha bavan images">
        <img class="p2" src="https://content.jdmagicbox.com/comp/villupuram/v5/9999p4146.4146.181101123321.g4v5/catalogue/hotel-vasantha-bhavan-ulundurpet-villupuram-restaurants-auv6lkql8y.jpg">
        <img class="p3" src="data:image/jpeg;base64,"></div>

        <ul>
            <li>Hotel Vasantha Bhavan is located opposite to the Ulundurpet Bus Stop.</li>
            <li>It is one of the famous veg hotel in ulundurpet.</li>
            <li>Vasanta Bhavan has been accredited with the ISO 22000:2005 quality certificate from QMS, a UK-based company.</li>
            <li>Apart from the restaurant division, Namma Veedu Vasanta Bhavan also undertakes catering orders for individuals and corporates. A Food and Beverage Manager assisted by a team of chefs, look after the health aspects.</li>
            <li>The committee not only works on the taste and the quality but also works on the nutrition value. </li>
            <li>Namma Veedu Vasanta Bhavan is also operating as the official caterers at companies such as Mahindra Satyam, Sutherland Global Services Limited, FL Smidth, Siemens Shared Services and the HCL Technologies.
            </li>
            <li>Vasanta Bhavan restaurant was started in Trichy by Patron Mr. A. Muthukrishnan[1].[2] Mr.A.Muthukrishnan started branches in Chennai. </li>
            <li>The chain of restaurants handled by Mr. M. Ravi was changed to Namma Veedu Vasanta Bhavan chain of restaurants. He is also the Vice President of the Tamil Nadu Hotels Association.

            </li>
            <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/cb/VBH_LOGO_JPEG.JPG/220px-VBH_LOGO_JPEG.JPG">

    </body>
</html>
